uniqueIssues.suggestedFix:
Use a darker text color that achieves at least 4.5:1 contrast on white. For example:
.price-table td:not(:first-child) {
    text-align: center;
    color: #2d2d2d; /* High-contrast on white */
    font-weight: 600;
}
If brand color is required, choose a darker shade that meets 4.5:1 and verify with a contrast checker.

Provide a non-color visual indicator for links (e.g., underline). For example:
.price-note a {
    color: #1a0dab; /* or another distinct color with sufficient contrast */
    text-decoration: underline;
}
Also consider adding a focus style:
.price-note a:focus {
    outline: 2px solid #1a0dab;
    outline-offset: 2px;
}

Assign a distinct link style that does not rely only on color. For example:
.price-note a {
    color: #1a0dab; /* distinct link color with sufficient contrast */
    text-decoration: underline;
    font-weight: 600; /* optional additional non-color cue */
}

Use a darker color for the section label that meets 4.5:1 against #faf9f7. For example:
.section-label {
    color: #2d2d2d;
}
If brand color must be used, choose a darker shade of the brand color that passes 4.5:1 and verify with a contrast checker.

Increase contrast for the price text. For example:
.room-price {
    color: #2d2d2d; /* High-contrast on white */
}
Alternatively, use a darker brand shade that achieves at least 3:1 for large text. Verify with a contrast checker.

Use a darker gray for sufficient contrast. For example:
.price-period {
    color: #666666; /* or #595959 */
}
Confirm with a contrast checker to ensure ≥4.5:1 on white.

Ensure hover state maintains sufficient contrast. For example:
.room-link:hover {
    color: #1a1a1a; /* Keep high contrast */
    text-decoration: underline; /* Optional non-color cue on hover */
}
Alternatively, use a darker brand shade that meets contrast requirements.

Remove the global outline reset and provide visible focus styles for interactive elements. For example:
/* Remove outline reset from the universal rule */
/* * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; } */
:focus-visible { outline: 3px solid #1a1a1a; outline-offset: 2px; }
a:focus-visible, button:focus-visible, [role="button"]:focus-visible, input:focus-visible, textarea:focus-visible { outline: 3px solid #1a1a1a; outline-offset: 2px; }

Provide a distinct, high-contrast link color and/or underline for links. For example:
a { color: #0a66c2; text-decoration: underline; }
a:hover, a:focus { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
a:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid #1a1a1a; outline-offset: 2px; }

Restore underlines for inline links, at least in body copy, and ensure they remain present on focus:
a { text-decoration: underline; }
a:hover, a:focus { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }

Use a darker color that reaches at least 4.5:1 against white. For example:
:root { --text-low-contrast: #666666; }
/* or */
.low-contrast-text { color: #595959; }

Use a higher contrast border (>= 3:1 against white) or a thicker/darker outline. For example:
input, textarea { border: 1px solid #767676; }
input:focus, textarea:focus { border-color: #1a1a1a; outline: 2px solid #1a1a1a; outline-offset: 2px; }

Increase contrast by using darker text or a darker button background. For example:
.btn-primary { color: #1a1a1a; }
/* or darken the gradient colors until white text reaches 4.5:1 */

Use a higher-contrast text color for outline buttons on light backgrounds. For example:
.btn-outline { color: #1a1a1a; border-color: #1a1a1a; }
/* or darken the brand gold significantly until contrast ≥ 4.5:1 */

Ensure hover state maintains sufficient contrast. For example:
.btn-outline:hover { background: var(--primary-gold); color: #1a1a1a; }
/* or darken the background color until white text reaches ≥ 4.5:1 */

